<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-11T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-11T10:00:00-05:00" n="918" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d918">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/2643: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-11T10:00:00-05:00">September 11, 1940—10
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 12:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>104. Department’s telegram No. 140, August 30, 5 p.m.<note n="69" xml:id="d918fn1">Not printed.</note> The Secretary of the Treasury
                            has just informed me that instead of a $15,000,000 loan the Government
                            now wants a $65,000,000 loan and that a detailed request will be
                            forwarded to Washington promptly. He of course does not favor the
                            loan.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>